ood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Chandos was born about 1275, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas Gregor."},"et":{"Abt 1275–":"umbes 1275–Surnud","1253–Male":"1253–Surnud","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","Abt 1275":"umbes 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Abt 1292":"umbes 1292","1292":"1292","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1275–":"noin 1275–Kuollut","1253–Male":"1253–Kuollut","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","Abt 1275":"noin 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Abt 1292":"noin 1292","1292":"1292","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1275–":"environ 1275–Décédée","1253–Male":"1253–Décédé","1292–Female":"1292–Décédée","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","Abt 1275":"environ 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Abt 1292":"environ 1292","1292":"1292","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Chandos est née environ 1275, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Thomas Gregor."},"de":{"Abt 1275–":"um 1275–Verstorben","1253–Male":"1253–Verstorben","1292–Female":"1292–Verstorben","1275–Female":"1275–Verstorben","Abt 1275":"um 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Abt 1292":"um 1292","1292":"1292","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Chandos wurde um 1275 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Thomas Gregor mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1275–":"about 1275–Desede","1253–Male":"1253–Desede","1292–Female":"1292–Desede","1275–Female":"1275–Desede","Abt 1275":"about 1275","1275":"1275","1253":"1253","Abt 1292":"about 1292","1292":"1292","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"Abt 1275–":"1275 körül–elhunyt","1253–Male":"1253–elhunyt","1292–Female":"1292–elhunyt","1275–Female":"1275–elhunyt","Abt 1275":"1275 körü